4 Jana Sharanara Hijack Purana is a C. Shi. Background: Religious Guru: Sanganabasavanna (discoverer of Ishtalinga) Emblem: Ishtalinga Disciple: Sharana Revanasiddha Emblem: Ishtalinga Religion: Lingayat Basavanna's contemporary Sharana Revanasiddha was falsely claimed by the Panchacharyas to have arisen in the Someshwara plant in Kollipaki and made Sharana a myth under the name Renukacharya. First, he wrote the Purana of Chaturacharya, and then he added another Acharya and wrote the fictional Shikhamani Purana for the Panchacharyas, claiming that they had incarnated for ages. Chaturacharyas were originally devotees of Basava. Their names are as follows: 4 Basava devotees Chaturacharyas 1) Revanasiddha => Renukaradhya 2) Marulasiddha => Marularadhya 3) Ekorama => Ekoramaradhya 4) Panditaradhya => Panditaradhya + Vishwaradhya => Vishwaradhya Panchacharya Ah, the incarnation of Panchacharya by stealing the names of four Sharanas?! Brief Philosophy Shikhamani: Religious Guru: Kailasapati Shiva, Rudra, Shankara, Mahadeva Emblem: Janivar Disciple: Mythological Renukacharya Emblem: Sthavaralinga World Gurus: Panchacharya Emblem: Ishtalinga (invented by Basavanna) Religion: *Veerashaiva (previously for recognition 5 times) *Hindu Dharma (year ago) *Hindu Veerashaiva Lingayat (from the day before) *Sanatana Veerashaiva Dharma (from yesterday) What is Maya?!
